														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-915923">
									

<p>No, I don't think I could. I don't have that good a grasp of neurology myself, and what I've written here was left vague on purpose partly to disguise that lack of knowledge. Besides that, I figure that the more detailed my explanation becomes, the more likely it will be that what I say becomes utter nonsense. Not to mention the fact that it wouldn't be an SCP if there weren't some mystery about how or why it works.</p>
<p>Part of the basis for this SCP idea is that neuroscience is a very young science, and a poorly understood one. There's a lot of stuff about the human brain that still has the character of "black-box" technology, even today. Twenty years ago, it was significantly worse. One of my college professors actually introduced a psychology class with the quote "Everything you learn in here will most likely be proven wrong, or at least somewhat inaccurate, within your lifetime," and based on what I've studied, I'm pretty confident that that statement is true.</p>

							</div>

								
					
