														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-916185">
									

<p>The way I see it, although 898 is a tool of the Foundation, it fits the basic criteria for an SCP in that it is a) Supernatural and/or extranormal in character, and b) may be an ongoing issue for the Foundation. It's comparable to <a href="/scp-061">SCP-061</a>, in that sense. Plus, it may become an active project again, someday, if the O5's see fit to start it up in the future.</p>
<p>"three (3) years" may seem arbitrary, but that's just because it really is arbitrary. Nevertheless, it's the format that is used throughout the site (I think). Consistency &gt; Reason.</p>
<p>Exposing only one person at a time was something they did in the early stages of testing, but that's no way to get a large body of data. Complicating matters is the fact that not everyone who received SCP-898 treatment responded to it in the same way. In fact, there were some fairly significant differences between subjects. That's part of the reason why the project was abandoned.</p>

							</div>

								
					
